&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge and an opportunity to shape the future of&lt;br /&gt;Stroke Care?&lt;br /&gt;East Lancs Hospitals NHS Trust is looking to appoint a Matron for Stroke&lt;br /&gt;Services&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting and challenging time within the Medicine for Older People&lt;br /&gt;directorate at East Lancashire Hospitals Trust and we are pleased to announce a&lt;br /&gt;post of Matron at the Royal Blackburn and Pendle Community Hospitals to lead and&lt;br /&gt;manage our progressive Stroke Services.&lt;br /&gt;We have a well-established and innovative Stroke team who provide Hyper Acute&lt;br /&gt;and Acute care as well as an out of hours specialist service that supports 24/7&lt;br /&gt;thrombolysis at the Royal Blackburn site and a Rehabilitation unit at Pendle&lt;br /&gt;Community Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;As the Matron you will provide clinical, professional and line management to the&lt;br /&gt;nursing teams. You will demonstrate effective leadership and continually monitor and&lt;br /&gt;strive to improve clinical standards ensuring excellent standards of performance in&lt;br /&gt;line with national SSNAP and local targets.&lt;br /&gt;You will need to be passionate about effectively motivating and developing the team&lt;br /&gt;to provide the very highest standards of care for all patients and ensuring the patient&lt;br /&gt;experience is positive.&lt;br /&gt;In return we offer a friendly supportive environment that values individuals in their&lt;br /&gt;personal and professional development and you will be supported Junior and&lt;br /&gt;Speciality doctors, Consultants Matrons, Ward Managers and nurses, Consultant&lt;br /&gt;Stroke Nurses and therapy teams as part of a multi-professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLaura LovedayJob titleADNSEmail addresslaura.loveday@elht.nhs.ukTelephone number83852Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or please contact Hazel Whittle Assistant Director of Nursing (Medicine and Emergency&lt;br /&gt;Care) on hazel.whittle@elht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
